  "original_title": "\u0db4\u0dcf\u0dc3\u0dca\u0db4\u0ddd\u0da7\u0dca \u0db4\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dcf \u0daf\u0dda\u0dc1\u0dd3\u0dba \u0d9a\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0dca\u0dba\u0dcf\u0dbd \u0db8\u0d9c\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dca \u0daf\u0dd2\u0db1\u0d9a\u0da7 100\u0d9a\u0da7 \u0d91\u0d9a\u0dca\u0daf\u0dd2\u0db1 \u0dc3\u0dda\u0dc0\u0dcf\u0dc0",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "100 per day by local passport offices for one-day service",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The department said that they are working to implement the one-day service at 100 per day through four local offices under the Department of Immigration and Emigration.",
        "Thus, the Matara, Kandy and Vavuniya offices provide one-day service to 100 applicants who have booked a date and time in advance. Accordingly. There is an opportunity to reserve a date and time by handing in the applications to the above mentioned offices through the www.immigration.gov.lk website."
      ],
